Core Structure & Key Concepts of ITIL 4
Here are the main components and ideas you want to internalize:

Concept	Description / Purpose
Service Value System (SVS)	This is the ‚Äúoperating model‚Äù of ITIL 4. It defines how all the components and activities of the organization work together to facilitate value creation via IT services. 
freshworks.com
+2
atlassian.com
+2
Guiding Principles	There are 7 principles intended to guide decision-making and behavior, regardless of process (e.g. Focus on value, Start where you are, Progress iteratively with feedback, Collaborate and promote visibility, Think and work holistically, Keep it simple and practical, Optimize and automate). 
diligent.com
+3
Wikipedia
+3
freshworks.com
+3
Practices	In ITIL 4, what used to be called ‚Äúprocesses/functions‚Äù are now called ‚Äúpractices‚Äù (to allow more flexibility). There are 34 practices categorized (General Management, Service Management, Technical Management). 
auditboard.com
