You said:
can i install NVIDIA¬Æ Jetson Orin‚Ñ¢ NX module on orin nano board?
ChatGPT said:
Excellent and very practical question ‚úÖ ‚Äî and here‚Äôs the clear technical answer:

üëâ No, you cannot directly install the NVIDIA Jetson Orin NX module on the Jetson Orin Nano Developer Kit carrier board ‚Äî at least not without a compatible carrier board.

Let‚Äôs break it down carefully üëá

üß© 1. Physical Compatibility
Both the Jetson Orin Nano and Jetson Orin NX modules use the same physical connector type (SO-DIMM 260-pin) and mechanical form factor, so in theory, they can fit the same socket.

However‚Ä¶
the Jetson Orin Nano Developer Kit‚Äôs carrier board is designed and power-limited for the Orin Nano module only, not the Orin NX.

‚ö° 2. Power & Thermal Differences
Module	Power	Cooling	Note
Orin Nano (8GB)	7‚Äì15W	Passive/Small active fan	Supported on Nano Dev Kit
Orin NX (16GB)	10‚Äì25W	Larger heatsink/fan required	Not supported on Nano Dev Kit
Orin NX (8GB)	10‚Äì25W	Same as above	Requires different power rail design
üí° Reason:
The Nano Dev Kit‚Äôs power delivery system (PDN) and cooling are not sufficient for the Orin NX‚Äôs higher draw and sustained workloads. The board can‚Äôt supply enough stable current for the NX module under load.

üß† 3. Software / Firmware Differences
The JetPack SDK image pre-installed for the Nano board has device tree, power management, and thermal profiles specific to the Nano module.

The Orin NX requires a different device tree and sometimes a different BSP (Board Support Package).

Plugging in the NX module to a Nano dev board without modification will likely result in boot failure or instability.

üß∞ 4. Supported Path if You Want to Upgrade
If you want to upgrade to Orin NX, you have two main options:

Option 1: Buy the Jetson Orin NX Developer Kit
It comes with a carrier board and thermal solution specifically designed for the NX.

Full compatibility with JetPack 6+, CUDA, TensorRT, DeepStream, etc.

You‚Äôll get up to 100 TOPS AI performance vs. 40 TOPS on Nano.

üëâ Best option if you want plug-and-play upgrade and full NVIDIA support.

Option 2: Use a Third-party Carrier Board
Companies like Seeed Studio, Connect Tech, Auvidea, and Forecr make universal carrier boards that support both Orin Nano and Orin NX modules.

Examples:

Auvidea JNX42

Seeed Jetson Orin Carrier Board

Connect Tech Quark Carrier

These boards can deliver up to 25W or more power, have extra I/O, and are physically interchangeable.

üí° TL;DR
Question	Answer
Can you plug Orin NX into Orin Nano Dev Kit?	‚ùå Not recommended / not supported
Why not?	Power, thermal, and BSP incompatibility
Do they share pin layout?	‚úÖ Yes (same 260-pin SO-DIMM connector)
How to upgrade?	Buy Orin NX Dev Kit or use a 3rd-party carrier board supporting both
Is data/code portable?	‚úÖ Yes ‚Äî your JetPack projects and Docker images will work on NX with minimal tweaks
Would you like me to recommend a compatible carrier board that supports both Orin Nano and NX (so you can upgrade later without buying a new kit)?

